President Biden delivered his State of the Union address, focusing on his economic agenda and unity agenda. He emphasized the need to build the economy from the bottom up and create good-paying jobs in infrastructure, manufacturing, and clean energy. Various union and labor leaders praised the President's commitment to workers and unions. They highlighted the passage of important legislation, such as the Chips and Science Act, the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act, and the Inflation Reduction Act. The President also addressed his unity agenda, which includes addressing the opioid crisis, mental health, supporting veterans, and ending cancer. He received support from a wide range of constituencies, including community leaders, business leaders, and faith-based organizations. The President's remarks were seen as a positive step towards addressing key issues and bringing people together.